ED FROM CLIENT: 1. Your niche/industry: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 2. List 3-5 competitors you admire or see as successful: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 3. Describe your ideal client in 2-3 sentences: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 4. What transformation do you deliver? Before state → After state: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 5. What makes your approach different (even slightly)? [CLIENT_RESPONSE] EXECUTION SEQUENCE: STEP 1: MARKET INTELLIGENCE SCAN - Analyze each competitor's positioning, offers, pricing, messaging - Identify market gaps and underserved segments - Score opportunities on: Market size, Competition level, Profit potential (1-10 scale) - Output: Market Opportunity Matrix with top 3 positioning recommendations STEP 2: AVATAR CRYSTALLIZATION Using the client's ideal client description, create 3 detailed avatars: - Avatar Name & Demographics - Day-in-the-life scenario - Top 5 pain points (ranked by urgency) - Top 5 desires (ranked by intensity) - Buying triggers and decision-making criteria - Common objections and skepticisms - Media consumption habits - Language patterns and terminology they use STEP 3: PAIN POINT HIERARCHY Create ranked list of 20 pain points with: - Pain point description - Urgency score (1-10) - Market demand indicator - Current solution inadequacy rating - Willingness to pay score STEP 4: UNIQUE MECHANISM DEVELOPMENT Based on client's approach, generate: - 5 proprietary framework name options (e.g., \"The 7-Day AI Launch Accelerator\") - Positioning statement for each - Trademark viability check - Differentiation strength score (1-10) DELIVERABLE FORMAT: - PDF Report: \"Your Market Domination Blueprint\" - Executive Summary (1 page) - Market Analysis (5-7 pages) - Avatar Profiles (3-4 pages) - Pain Point Hierarchy (2-3 pages) - Unique Mechanism Options (2-3 pages) - Recommended Path Forward (1 page) QUALITY GATES: - All recommendations must be backed by data/research - Language must match target avatar's vocabulary - Positioning must create clear blue ocean opportunity - Client should feel \"This is exactly what I needed to see\" Begin analysis now. DAY 2: IRRESISTIBLE OFFER ARCHITECTURE Feature Breakdown Table Feature Component\tWhat It Does\tClient Input Required\tAI Output Delivered\tExpected Outcome\tSupporting Data/Rationale Offer Stack Builder\tCreates premium offer with core + bonuses using value stacking principles\tDesired price point, what they can deliver, time commitment\tComplete offer structure with 8-12 components valued individually\t$10,000+ perceived value offer\tJay Abraham's value stacking increases perceived value 5-10x Pricing Psychology Engine\tDetermines optimal price point using market data + positioning\tCurrent market rates, desired positioning (premium/mid/entry)\t3 pricing strategies with conversion projections and profit modeling\tMaximum profit with ethical pricing\tPrice optimization can increase revenue 40-300% without losing customers Guarantee Architect\tCreates powerful, risk-reversing guarantee that removes all buying friction\tClient's confidence level, what results they can promise\t3-5 guarantee options from standard to outrageous\tEliminates #1 purchase objection\tStrong guarantees increase conversion 20-40% with <5% refund rates Scarcity & Urgency Mechanisms\tBuilds authentic reasons to buy now vs. later\tLaunch timeline, capacity limits, bonus expirations\tScarcity framework with ethical urgency drivers\t3-5x increase in immediate purchases\tFrank Kern: \"Without urgency, 85% of buyers will procrastinate indefinitely\" AI Agent Prompt for Day 2: Copy ROLE: You are an elite offer architect combining Jay Abraham's strategy of preeminence and value multiplication, Frank Kern's direct response offer creation, and Aaron Fletcher's premium positioning frameworks. TASK: Create an irresistible, premium-priced coaching offer for [CLIENT_NAME] that their avatar cannot say no to. INPUT DATA REQUIRED FROM CLIENT: 1. Desired price point range: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 2. Time commitment you can deliver (hours/week, program length): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 3. Core deliverables you want to include (coaching calls, materials, etc.): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 4. What results can you confidently guarantee (or help achieve): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 5. Any capacity limitations (max clients, launch windows): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 6. Additional value you can add (templates, tools, bonuses, access): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] REFERENCE DATA: - Day 1 Avatar profiles - Pain point hierarchy - Unique mechanism name (selected by client) EXECUTION SEQUENCE: STEP 1: CORE OFFER FOUNDATION Create the main program structure: - Program name incorporating unique mechanism - Core transformation promise (specific, measurable, time-bound) - Program duration and delivery format - Main components (modules, sessions, materials) - Value each component independently ($X value) STEP 2: STRATEGIC BONUS STACK Add 5-8 bonuses that: - Accelerate results (speed) - Remove obstacles (ease) - Provide additional tools (completeness) - Add social proof (credibility) Each bonus must: - Solve a specific pain point from Day 1 analysis - Have clear standalone value ($X value) - Be deliverable without huge time investment - Names must be benefit-driven (not feature-driven) STEP 3: VALUE STACKING ARCHITECTURE Create the \"Total Value Breakdown\": - Core Program: $X - Bonus 1: $X - Bonus 2: $X - [continue for all bonuses] - Total Value: $XX,XXX - Your Investment Today: $X,XXX - Savings: $X,XXX (XX%) STEP 4: PRICING STRATEGY MATRIX Provide 3 pricing options with analysis: OPTION A: Premium Single Pay - Price: $[AMOUNT] - Positioning: Exclusive, high-commitment clients - Projected conversion rate: X% - Projected revenue per 100 leads: $X OPTION B: Payment Plan - Price: [X] payments of $[AMOUNT] = $[TOTAL] - Positioning: Accessible premium - Projected conversion rate: X% - Projected revenue per 100 leads: $X OPTION C: Tiered Pricing (Good/Better/Best) - Price points and differentiation - Projected distribution and revenue Recommend optimal strategy based on avatar buying behavior. STEP 5: RISK REVERSAL GUARANTEE CREATION Develop 3 guarantee options: GUARANTEE OPTION 1: Standard Money-Back \"If you don't [achieve specific result] within [timeframe], we'll refund 100% of your investment\" GUARANTEE OPTION 2: Results Guarantee \"We guarantee you'll [specific outcome] or we'll work with you free until you do\" GUARANTEE OPTION 3: Outrageous Guarantee (Frank Kern style) \"If you [complete the program requirements] and don't [get results], we'll refund your money AND pay you $[AMOUNT] for wasting your time\" Include activation criteria for each. STEP 6: SCARCITY & URGENCY FRAMEWORK Create authentic urgency mechanisms: - Limited enrollment (based on actual capacity) - Fast-action bonuses (expire in X days) - Price increase schedule - Seasonal/timely relevance - Cohort start dates DELIVERABLE FORMAT: - PDF Document: \"Your Million-Dollar Offer Blueprint\" - Offer Overview (1 page) - Complete Offer Stack (2-3 pages) - Pricing Strategy Analysis (2 pages) - Guarantee Options (1-2 pages) - Urgency Mechanisms (1 page) - Sales Page Outline (2-3 pages) QUALITY GATES: - Total perceived value must be 10-20x the asking price - Every bonus must solve a real pain point from Day 1 - Pricing must be premium but achievable for avatar - Guarantee must feel safe but not be easily exploited - Urgency must be authentic and ethical Begin offer creation now. DAY 3: SALES PAGE & VSL COPY GENERATION Feature Breakdown Table Feature Component\tWhat It Does\tClient Input Required\tAI Output Delivered\tExpected Outcome\tSupporting Data/Rationale Headline Forge\tCreates 10 high-converting headline variations using proven formulas\tTop benefit, unique mechanism name, biggest pain point\t10 headline options tested against conversion data\tAttention-grabbing first impression\tHeadlines account for 80% of ad effectiveness (David Ogilvy) Story-Selling Script Writer\tCrafts origin story or case study that creates emotional connection\tClient's story OR client 