Agitate top 3 pain points from Day 1 - Make problem feel urgent and expensive - Position current solutions as inadequate - 300-400 words SECTION 6: Solution Introduction \"What if there was a better way? There is. It's called [Unique Mechanism]...\" - Introduce unique mechanism - Explain why it's different - Preview the transformation - 200-300 words SECTION 7: Proof & Credibility - Client results/testimonials (if available) - Your credentials/experience - Statistical proof - 150-200 words SECTION 8: \"What You're Getting\" - Offer Stack Present complete offer from Day 2: - Core program breakdown - Each bonus with benefit-driven description - Value stack presentation - 400-600 words SECTION 9: Bullet Fascination Section Create 50+ bullets in categories: - What you'll discover: [15 bullets] - What you'll be able to do: [15 bullets] - Secrets you'll learn: [10 bullets] - What this means for you: [10 bullets] SECTION 10: Price Reveal - Value stack recap - \"Total Value: $XX,XXX\" - \"Your investment today: $X,XXX\" - Payment options - 100-150 words SECTION 11: Guarantee [Use selected guarantee from Day 2] - State guarantee clearly - Explain why you can make this guarantee - Remove risk perception - 150-200 words SECTION 12: Objection Handling / FAQ Address top 10 objections: - \"Is this right for me?\" - \"I don't have time\" - \"I've tried other things that didn't work\" - \"What if I don't get results?\" - [Continue based on client's input] Each answer: 75-100 words SECTION 13: Urgency Restatement - Scarcity elements from Day 2 - Countdown to bonus expiration - Limited enrollment - 100-150 words SECTION 14: Final CTA - Direct command to action - Repeat main benefit - No-risk reminder - 50-75 words SECTION 15: PS Section (3 PS statements) - PS1: Restate main benefit and urgency - PS2: Social proof element - PS3: Final risk reversal reminder STEP 4: VSL SCRIPT CREATION (15-20 MINUTE VIDEO) [MINUTE 0-1: PATTERN INTERRUPT & HOOK] \"Hey, let me ask you something... [provocative question]\" - Hook statement - Permission to continue - What this video is about [MINUTE 1-3: CREDIBILITY & RELATABILITY] - Brief intro of who you are - Why you understand their problem - Preview of what's coming [MINUTE 3-8: PROBLEM AMPLIFICATION] - Deep dive into pain points - \"You've probably tried [common solutions]...\" - Why those don't work - Cost of staying stuck (emotional + financial) [MINUTE 8-10: SOLUTION REVEAL] - Introduce unique mechanism - Explain the framework - Why it's different - Quick proof (case study or result) [MINUTE 10-14: THE OFFER] - Walk through what they get - Value stack presentation - Bonuses explained - Price reveal with context [MINUTE 14-16: RISK REVERSAL] - Guarantee explanation - Why you can promise this - Urgency/scarcity elements [MINUTE 16-18: OBJECTION HANDLING] - \"Now you might be thinking...\" - Address top 3-5 objections - Reframe each one [MINUTE 18-20: FINAL CTA] - Direct call to action - Recap of main benefit - What happens next - Final urgency reminder - \"Click the button below right now\" [Include timing markers, slide prompts, tonality notes] DELIVERABLE FORMAT: - PDF: \"Your Sales Copy Arsenal\" - 10 Headline Options (1 page) - 3 Story Variations (3-4 pages) - Complete Sales Page Copy (12-18 pages) - 50+ Bullet Library (2-3 pages) - FAQ/Objection Handling (2-3 pages) - VSL Script with timing (8-12 pages) - 10 CTA Variations (1 page) QUALITY GATES: - Copy must match avatar's language from Day 1 - Every claim must be believable and provable - Objections must be handled preemptively - Emotional + logical appeal balance - Urgency must feel authentic - Client should say \"This sounds exactly like me\" Begin copywriting now. DAY 4: EMAIL SEQUENCE & LAUNCH AUTOMATION Feature Breakdown Table Feature Component\tWhat It Does\tClient Input Required\tAI Output Delivered\tExpected Outcome\tSupporting Data/Rationale Pre-Launch Sequence\t5-7 emails to warm up list before offer reveal\tList size, relationship level with audience, current engagement\t7-email pre-launch sequence with subject lines and preview text\tAudience primed and excited before offer drops\tPre-launch sequences increase launch revenue 40-150% Launch Week Blitz\t8-12 emails during open cart period hitting different angles\tLaunch duration, cart open/close dates\tComplete launch email sequence with daily sending schedule\tMaximized conversion throughout launch window\tEmail frequency during launch drives 60-70% of sales Objection-Specific Emails\tDedicated emails addressing each major objection\tTop 5 objections from client + Day 1 data\t5 objection-focused emails with stories and reframes\tConverts fence-sitters into buyers\tObjection emails convert 15-25% of non-responders Abandoned Cart Recovery\tAutomated sequence for those who clicked but didn't buy\tNone needed (automated)\t3-email cart abandonment sequence\tRecovers 10-30% of lost sales\tCart recovery emails generate 15-30% additional revenue Social Proof Amplifier\tCase study/testimonial-focused emails\tAny client wins, results, testimonials\t3-5 social proof emails with different angles\tBuilds trust and overcomes skepticism\tSocial proof emails increase conversion 10-20% Deadline & Scarcity Escalation\tFinal 48-hour countdown sequence\tCart close date/time\t5-email final countdown sequence (48hr, 24hr, 12hr, 6hr, 1hr)\t40-60% of sales happen in final 48 hours\tLast-minute urgency drives final conversion surge AI Agent Prompt for Day 4: Copy ROLE: You are an elite email marketing strategist combining Frank Kern's product launch formula, Jeff Walker's launch sequence methodology, and Aaron Fletcher's automated conversion systems. TASK: Create a complete email sequence for [CLIENT_NAME]'s program launch that maximizes revenue through strategic sequencing and psychological triggers. INPUT DATA REQUIRED FROM CLIENT: 1. Your email list size and engagement level (warm/cold/mixed): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 2. Relationship with list (how often you email, your typical style): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 3. Launch timeline - how many days will cart be open?: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 4. Do you have any client testimonials or results to share?: [CLIENT_RESPONSE] 5. Your email voice (casual/professional, long/short, story-driven/direct): [CLIENT_RESPONSE] REFERENCE DATA: - Day 1: Avatar profiles, pain points - Day 2: Complete offer, guarantee, urgency elements - Day 3: Stories, bullets, objection handling EXECUTION SEQUENCE: STEP 1: PRE-LAUNCH SEQUENCE (7 DAYS BEFORE CART OPENS) EMAIL 1: \"The Announcement\" (Day -7) Subject: [Something big is coming...] Preview text: [Curiosity driver] Content structure: - Personal greeting - \"I've been working on something special...\" - Tease the transformation without revealing offer - Build curiosity about what's coming - No ask, just awareness [300-400 words] EMAIL 2: \"The Problem Deep Dive\" (Day -6) Subject: [Problem-focused, relatable] Preview text: [Pain point validation] Content structure: - Empathy-first opening - Deep dive into main pain point from Day 1 - \"This is costing you more than you realize...\" - Hint that solution is coming - Soft tease [400-500 words] EMAIL 3: \"What Doesn't Work (And Why)\" (Day -5) Subject: [Authority/contrarian angle] Preview text: [Challenge conventional wisdom] Content structure: - Address common failed solutions - Explain why they fail - Position your unique mechanism as different - More anticipation building [350-450 words] EMAIL 4: \"The Origin Story\" (Day -4) Subject: [Personal/vulnerable] Preview text: [Story hook] Content structure: - Use origin story from Day 3 - Show your transformation - Connect their pain to your past pain - Preview that you'll share the solution soon [500-700 words] EMAIL 5: \"Case Study Proof\" (Day -3) Subject: [Result-focused, specific] Preview text: [Tangible outcome] Content structure: - Client success story - Before → Process → After - Specific results and timeframe - \"This is what's possible...\" - Announce cart opens in 2 days [400-500 words] EMAIL 6: \"Unique Mechanism Revealed\" (Day -2) Subject: [Curiosity + value] Preview text: [Mechanism tease] Content structure: - Reveal your unique mechanism/framework - Explain how it works (high level) - Why it's different from everything else - Preview of what's in the offer - \"Tomorrow you'll get first access...\" [450-550 words] EMAIL 7: \"Opens Tomorrow + FAQ\" (Day -1) Subject: [Urgency + preparation] Preview text: [Final prep before launch] Content structure: - Cart opens tomorrow at [TIME] - Quick recap of what's coming - Address 3-5 pre-objections - Price range preview (manage expectations) - \"Set your alarm\" style urgency [300-400 words] STEP 2: LAUNCH WEEK SEQUENCE (CART OPEN) EMAIL 8: \"CART OPEN - Full Offer Reveal\" (Day 0, Morning) Subject: [Direct, clear, exciting] Preview text: [Main benefit + urgency] Content structure: - \"It's here!\" - Complete offer overview - What's included (summarized) - Price reveal - Guarantee - Clear CTA to sales page - Urgency reminder (cart closes in X days) [600-800 words] EMAIL 9: \"What You'll Achieve\" (Day 0, Evening) Subject: [Transformation-focused] Preview text: [Specific outcome] Content structure: - Focus on life after transformation - Paint vivid picture using Day 3 future pacing - Connect to deep desires from Day 1 - Link to sales page - \"Don't wait\" urgency [400-500 words] EMAIL 10: \"Bonus Stack Spotlight\" (Day 1) Subject: [Value-focused] Preview text: [Bonus highlight] Content structure: - Deep dive into bonuses - Why each one accelerates results - Total value breakdown - \"These bonuses alone are worth...\" - Fast action bonus reminder (if applicable) - CTA [450-550 words] EMAIL 11: \"Social Proof Avalanche\" (Day 2) Subject: [Results/testimonial focused] Preview text: [Powerful result snippet] Content structure: - Multiple client wins/testimonials - Different avatars/situations - \"People just like you are getting results...\" - Create FOMO - CTA [500-600 words] EMAIL 12: \"Objection Buster 1 - 'I don't have time'\" (Day 3) Subject: [Objection-addressing] Preview text: [Time-saving angle] Content structure: - Acknowledge objection empathetically - Reframe with story or logic - Show how program saves time - \"What's the cost of not finding time?\" - CTA [400-500 words] EMAIL 13: \"Objection Buster 2 - 'I've tried other things'\" (Day 4) Subject: [Differentiation angle] Preview text: [Why this is different] Content structure: - Validate their past failures - Explain why those failed - Position unique mechanism as solution - Risk reversal (guarantee) - CTA [400-500 words] EMAIL 14: \"Objection Buster 3 - 'Can I really do this?'\" (Day 5) Subject: [Confidence-building] Preview text: [Relatability] Content structure: - Address imposter syndrome/doubt - \"You don't need to be [expert level]...\" - Show how program removes complexity - Success stories from \"unlikely\" people - CTA [450-550 words] STEP 3: FINAL 48-HOUR COUNTDOWN EMAIL 15: \"48 Hours Left\" (Day 6, Morning) Subject: [Urgency + scarcity] Preview text: [Deadline reminder] Content structure: - Time warning - Recap of main transformation - Spots filling/bonuses expiring - \"This is your last chance...\" - Strong CTA [300-400 words] EMAIL 16: \"24 Hours - What You'll Miss\" (Day 7, Morning) Subject: [Loss aversion] Preview text: [What's at stake] Content structure: - Fear of missing out angle - Paint picture of regret - Cost of inaction - Contrast with transformation - Urgent CTA [400-500 words] EMAIL 17: \"12 Hours - Real Talk\" (Day 7, Noon) Subject: [Personal, direct] Preview text: [Final persuasion] Content structure: - Heart-to-heart message - Why you created this - Who it's perfect for (and who it's not) - Final objection handling - \"No regrets\" positioning - CTA [500-600 words] EMAIL 18: \"6 Hours - Bonuses Expiring\" (Day 7, 6PM) Subject: [Specific urgency] Preview text: [Bonus expiration] Content structure: - Focus on expiring bonuses - Value disappearing - Quick decision framework - Guarantee reminder - CTA [250-350 words] EMAIL 19: \"FINAL CALL - 1 Hour Left\" (Day 7, 11PM) Subject: [URGENT - final chance] Preview text: [Last call] Content structure: - Brief, direct, urgent - \"This is it\" - One-sentence benefit reminder - Link - \"Cart closes at midnight\" [150-200 words] STEP 4: ABANDONED CART SEQUENCE EMAIL 20: \"I noticed you were interested...\" (1 hour after cart close) Subject: [Curiosity + concern] Preview text: [Second chance tease] Content structure: - \"I noticed you visited the page but didn't join...\" - Ask if they had questions - Offer to answer concerns - Limited reopening (24-48 hours) - CTA [300-400 words] EMAIL 21: \"My personal guarantee to you\" (12 hours later) Subject: [Risk reversal focus] Preview text: [Guarantee emphasis] Content structure: - Deep dive into guarantee - Remove ALL perceived risk - \"What do you have to lose?\" - Testimonial about overcoming doubt - CTA [400-500 words] EMAIL 22: \"Final 24 hours - Special extension\" (24 hours after initial cart close) Subject: [Last-last chance] Preview text: [Extension ending] Content structure: - Limited extension ends tomorrow - No more chances after this - Quick recap of offer - Personal note - Final CTA [300-400 words] DELIVERABLE FORMAT: - PDF: \"Your Complete Launch Email Playbook\" - Pre-Launch Sequence (7 emails) with schedule - Launch Week Sequence (12 emails) with schedule - Countdown Sequence (5 emails) with timing - Cart Abandonment Sequence (3 emails) with triggers - Subject Line Library (100+ variations) - Email sending schedule/calendar - Technical setup instructions QUALITY GATES: - Each email must have one primary goal - Subject lines must drive opens (curiosity/benefit/urgency) - Preview text must complement subject - Emails must flow logically in sequence - Voice must match client's style - CTAs must be clear and varied - Every email needs reason to send (value/info/urgency) Begin email sequence creation now. DAY 5: VISUAL ASSETS & BRAND IDENTITY